374
00:41:43,217 --> 00:41:43,938
[SPEAKER_05]: on the street.

375
00:41:44,238 --> 00:41:51,261
[SPEAKER_05]: And maybe there's an easier way to say all of that that is less outdated.

376
00:41:52,501 --> 00:42:09,336
[SPEAKER_05]: But I don't, you know, I wouldn't mind just one more time seeing what you had suggested, but I don't mind maybe sending along what we have now, plus what you had suggested and seeing what legal counsel, maybe they have some sort of form language that might line up with something more modern.

377
00:42:11,618 --> 00:42:12,599
[SPEAKER_05]: But in general, I don't.

378
00:42:13,346 --> 00:42:14,247
[SPEAKER_05]: I don't think we're far up.

379
00:42:14,467 --> 00:42:25,954
[SPEAKER_05]: I think we want to maintain the intent of what exists here, but say it in a way that it's easier for people to read and understand it, and that it's more related to the issues that we have today versus when this was written.

380
00:42:25,994 --> 00:42:31,238
[SPEAKER_05]: I'm pretty sure all of this predates the 74 revision, 1974 ordinance revision.

381
